{
  "$comment": "FC17.9(a) (D-CSUBSET-C11-THREADS-HEADER): +the kernel32 primitives the pe64 <threads.h> synth shim (src/mir/merge/synth_threads_shim.cpp) lowers over — CONDITION_VARIABLE (8B, mirrors SRWLOCK) + Initialize/Wake/WakeAll ConditionVariable + SleepConditionVariableCS (cnd_*), Fls Alloc/GetValue/SetValue/Free (tss_* — FlsAlloc's PFLS_CALLBACK_FUNCTION dtor == C11 tss_dtor_t, real destructor semantics), SwitchToThread (thrd_yield), ExitThread (thrd_exit), GetExitCodeThread (thrd_join), GetCurrentThread (thrd_current). All real kernel32 exports; the CriticalSection family + CreateThread/CloseHandle/WaitForSingleObject/Sleep (mtx_*/thrd_join) already shipped below. These are ALSO on-demand imported by the synth pass for a threads.h-only TU (which does not #include <windows.h>), deduped by name. | c116a (the SEH AV witness): +VirtualAlloc/VirtualFree (real kernel32 exports) + EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION=0xC0000005 / MEM_COMMIT=0x1000 / MEM_RESERVE=0x2000 / MEM_RELEASE=0x8000 / PAGE_NOACCESS=0x01 (SDK-verified) — the examples/c-subset/seh_catch_av witness commits a PAGE_NOACCESS page, reads it (AV), and catches via __except(GetExceptionCode()==EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION). __C_specific_handler is NOT shipped in symbols (the c101 0xC0000139 eager-import law) — the SEH funclet pass synthesizes its msvcrt import on demand when a scope table is emitted. | c106 (the shell.c batch): +the windirent trio (FindFirstFileW/FindNextFileW/FindClose) + console surface (GetStdHandle/GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo/WriteConsoleW/Get+SetConsoleMode) + GetSystemTime/SystemTimeToFileTime/SetFileTime/SetCurrentDirectoryW/SetConsoleCtrlHandler(PHANDLER_ROUTINE fn-ptr)/GetSystemTimePreciseAsFileTime/GetCurrentProcess/DebugBreak/LoadLibraryA (dumpbin-verified kernel32) + SYSTEMTIME/WIN32_FIND_DATAW(592B)/ULARGE_INTEGER (c107 D-FFI-DESCRIPTOR-UNION-OVERLAY: an explicit-offset OVERLAP struct {QuadPart u64@0, LowPart u32@0, HighPart u32@4}, size 8 — shell.c fileTimeToUnixTime writes the two u32 halves + reads the u64 whole; the `offset` field + type-text `@off` make the structs entry + the bare typedef canonicalize to ONE TypeId)/COORD/SMALL_RECT/CONSOLE_SCREEN_BUFFER_INFO + STD_*_HANDLE/ENABLE_VIRTUAL_TERMINAL_PROCESSING/FILE_WRITE_ATTRIBUTES/FILE_FLAG_BACKUP_SEMANTICS/CTRL_C_EVENT + TEXT(x)->x/LoadLibrary->LoadLibraryA (ANSI arms) + LPFILETIME typed pointee. | Neutral shipped <windows.h> (Win32) SKELETON — c95 (the FLIP-AND-UNBLOCK cycle of the Windows-host sub-arc). Predefining `_WIN32` (pe-gated, c-subset.lang.json) makes sqlite's amalgamation select its OWN os_win.c VFS (SQLITE_OS_WIN) instead of os_unix. os_win.c then needs the Win32 TYPE + STRUCT + CONSTANT vocabulary to PARSE; this descriptor supplies exactly that surface (the 13 core types + the 6 field-bearing records os_win.c reads members of + the constants it references). `availableObjectFormats:[pe]` — a Win32 header is meaningless on elf/macho (a reference there fails loud). `library:{pe:kernel32.dll}` — the eventual kernel32 import library (pe already imports kernel32 for ExitProcess). ★ SCOPE (c95): enough that os_win.c PARSES. The kernel32 FUNCTION declarations (the aSyscall[] table) were DEFERRED to c96+ and are shipped incrementally in the `symbols` block: ★ c101 (2026-07-04) shipped the SYNC slice — the `structs` SRWLOCK (8B) + CRITICAL_SECTION (RTL_CRITICAL_SECTION, 40B on x64) + 9 mutex fns (Initialize/Delete/Enter/Leave/TryEnter*CriticalSection + Initialize/Acquire/Release/TryAcquire*SRWLockExclusive), all real kernel32 exports (NTDLL forwarders). ★ c102 (2026-07-04) shipped the FILE/HEAP/TIME batch — 47 more kernel32 fns (CreateFileW/DeleteFileW/ReadFile/WriteFile/SetFilePointerEx/SetEndOfFile/FlushFileBuffers/GetFileSizeEx/GetFileAttributes[Ex]W/GetFullPathNameW/GetTempPathW/AreFileApisANSI/LockFileEx/UnlockFileEx/CloseHandle; Heap Create/Destroy/Alloc/ReAlloc/Free/Size/Compact/Validate/GetProcessHeap; CreateFileMappingW/MapViewOfFile/UnmapViewOfFile/FlushViewOfFile; LoadLibraryW/FreeLibrary/GetProcAddress; GetLastError/FormatMessageW/LocalFree/OutputDebugStringA; GetSystemInfo/GetSystemTimeAsFileTime/GetTickCount64/QueryPerformanceCounter/Sleep; GetCurrentProcessId/GetCurrentThreadId/WaitForSingleObject[Ex]; MultiByteToWideChar/WideCharToMultiByte) + 15 constants (CP_ACP/OEMCP/UTF8 codepages, WAIT_IO_COMPLETION=STATUS_USER_APC=192, NO_ERROR + 11 ERROR_* codes — all SDK-verified against shared/winerror.h, um/winnls.h, um/minwinbase.h of SDK 10.0.26100.0). ALL 47 SDK-verified real kernel32 exports via `dumpbin /exports` of the system kernel32.dll — HeapAlloc/HeapReAlloc/HeapSize are FORWARDER exports (→ NTDLL.Rtl*), loader-valid exactly like c101's AcquireSRWLockExclusive (a proven-green forwarder). Signatures are the sqlite os_win aSyscall[] WINAPI casts (ground truth); SetFilePointerEx's by-value LARGE_INTEGER (8B union) → i64; FormatMessageW's va_list* → ptr<void>. Remaining pe64 undefined: __umulh + InterlockedCompareExchange (x64 INTRINSICS, not kernel32 exports) → c103 builtin cycle. ★ NOTE: `InterlockedCompareExchange` (sqlite's winMutex atomic) is an x64 INTRINSIC (`lock cmpxchg`), NOT a kernel32 export — NEVER shipped in `symbols`: DSS EAGER-IMPORTS a descriptor's symbols for ANY program that `#include`s it, so a non-export symbol in `symbols` breaks the pe loader of every such program (STATUS_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND 0xC0000139 — it broke the windows_predefine_macro example when c101 tried). ★ c104 (D-CSUBSET-INTRINSIC-ATOMIC-CAS) ships it the way the REAL Windows SDK does: a `macros` entry `InterlockedCompareExchange` → `_InterlockedCompareExchange` (the winnt.h convention), where the underscore name is a DSS BUILTIN (c-subset.lang.json builtinFunctions, lowering:atomic_cas → x86 `lock cmpxchg` / arm64 LDAXR-STLXR loop). Including <windows.h> makes `#if defined(InterlockedCompareExchange)` TRUE → sqlite's aSyscall entry takes the `(SYSCALL)0` direct-intrinsic path and every call site expands to the builtin. TYPE MAPPINGS: HANDLE/LPVOID/LPCVOID/HMODULE/HLOCAL/FARPROC and the LP*_ pointer types → ptr<void> (Win32 opaque handles + C pointer coercion); LPCSTR/LPSTR → ptr<char> (ANSI); LPCWSTR/LPWSTR → ptr<u16> (UTF-16, WCHAR=u16); DWORD/UINT/ULONG → u32; LONG/BOOL/INT → i32; SIZE_T/ULONGLONG → u64; WCHAR → u16; VOID → void (the `(VOID)` empty prototype). GET_FILEEX_INFO_LEVELS is an enum → i32. LLP64 note: Win32 `LONG` is 32-bit (i32) even on 64-bit Windows (unlike POSIX `long`); the 64-bit forms use ULONGLONG/LARGE_INTEGER, so no `long`-width axis is needed here. STRUCT LAYOUTS (natural C alignment, the layout engine derives offsets from field sizes — matching the real windows.h records os_win reads): OVERLAPPED flattens its anonymous Offset/OffsetHigh union-struct (os_win writes .Offset/.OffsetHigh/.hEvent) → 32B; LARGE_INTEGER is modeled as a struct {i64 QuadPart} (os_win only ever touches .QuadPart, the widest 8B union member — a true `union` needs a descriptor `unions` block, out of c95 scope) → 8B; SYSTEM_INFO carries the real field order so .dwPageSize@4 / .dwAllocationGranularity@40 land correctly; FILETIME {u32,u32}=8B; WIN32_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DATA {dwFileAttributes, 3×FILETIME, nFileSizeHigh, nFileSizeLow}=36B (os_win reads .dwFileAttributes/.nFileSizeHigh/.nFileSizeLow). Each record is ALSO a bare typedef (os_win declares `OVERLAPPED ovlp;` without the `struct` keyword) whose inline `struct \"Name\"{…}` interns to the SAME TypeId as the structs-block entry (name + field-types identity), so the injected field scope resolves .member. CONSTANT values verified against the Windows SDK headers (winnt.h/winbase.h/fileapi.h/handleapi.h/memoryapi.h/errhandlingapi.h/winerror.h).",
